Sex: Females more likely to experience depressive symptoms.

May be b/c of biological susceptibility, lower baseline self-esteem, higher likelihood of having experienced interpersonal violence, exposure to stress b/c of gender inequity.


Age: Higher depression in older children.

May be b/c of puberty and hormonal changes, as well as social isolation b/c kids this age are especially reliant on socialization with peers.




Anxiety:

Time: Longer the pandemic went on, the worse things got

