Literature Review

Topics of PCSC:

Mostly focused on sexual anatomy rather than sexual activity (Ritchwood et al., 2018).

There is a significant degree of embarassment in talking about sexual activity; less so with anatomy (Ogle, Glasier, \& Riley, 2008).


Gender determines topics; girls get more info on pregnancy, relationships, biology, and abstinence than males do (Flores \& Barroso, 2017; Kim \& Ward, 2007; Wilson \& Koo, 2010).


